This paper discusses the use of deep neural networks in analyzing the function space of correlated embeddings of pairs of random variables. This topic is closely related to machine learning and data analysis, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses information theory and its application to this problem, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of these embeddings in classification and multi-modal learning, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), or cs.ST (Statistics) sub-categories. Overall, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG, followed by cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.CV, and cs.ST.
